  "prompt": "Has anyone survived a plane crash?",
  "response": "Yes, there have been several instances where individuals have survived plane crashes. Survival can depend on a range of factors including the severity of the crash, the location, the type of aircraft, and timely rescue operations. Notable survival cases include:\n\n1. **Vesna Vulovi\u0107 (1972)**: She holds the Guinness World Record for surviving the highest fall without a parachute. She was a flight attendant on JAT Airways, and the DC-9 aircraft she was on exploded at 33,000 feet. She survived with serious injuries.\n\n2. **Miracle on the Hudson (2009)**: US Airways Flight 1549, piloted by Captain Chesley \"Sully\" Sullenberger, performed an emergency landing on the Hudson River after both engines failed due to bird strikes. All 155 passengers and crew survived.\n\n3. **Andes Survivors (1972)**: After a crash in the Andes Mountains, 16 of the 45 passengers survived for 72 days before being rescued. Their story was famously told in the book \"Alive.\"\n\nThese cases are reminders of the complex interplay of skill, technology, and circumstances in aviation safety.",
